ins of the literature in the area of heterodoxy.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aTheology. 4aAlte Kirche. 4aApokrpyhen. 4aKopten /Religion. 4aMaria. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aApocrypha.  aMaria.  acoptic religion.  aearly church.1 aFörster, Hans, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2008z9783110209280oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311018227940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311019329940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110193299423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110193299/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014